[00:08.60]I lift my eyes, the stars are burning
[00:13.83]Endless light across the dark
[00:19.06]Time and space are bending, turning
[00:24.29]Every orbit marks Your mark
[00:29.52]I am small, a breath, a moment
[00:34.75]Here and gone before I know it
[00:39.98]Yet You speak and worlds awaken
[00:45.21]At the whisper of Your voice
[00:50.44]How big is our God, how wide, how strong
[00:55.67]He holds the night, He holds the dawn
[01:00.90]I am dust, I am days
[01:06.12]Still You know my name
[01:11.35]Planets spin in perfect motion
[01:16.58]Every star obeys Your law
[01:21.81]From the depths of every ocean
[01:27.04]To the sparrow when it falls
[01:32.27]You who measure out the heavens
[01:37.50]Chose the cross, the nails, the grave
[01:42.73]You stepped down into our weakness
[01:47.96]So the lost could now be saved
[01:53.19]How big is our God, how deep His reign
[01:58.42]The cosmos bends before His name
[02:03.65]I am small, yet fully known
[02:08.88]A child You call Your own
[02:14.11]If the stars cry out Your glory
[02:19.34]If the skies declare Your worth
[02:24.57]Who am I that You would love me
[02:29.80]Still You came to save this earth
[02:35.03]Bigger than the endless ages
[02:40.26]Stronger than the grave and death
[02:45.49]Yet You’re closer than my heartbeat
[02:50.72]Closer than my breath
[02:55.94]How big is our God, eternal King
[03:01.17]From silent space to everything
[03:06.40]I am small, yet not unseen
[03:11.63]Held in what You’ve always been
[03:16.86]How big is our God, let all proclaim
[03:22.09]The stars, the skies, the earth, His name
